The doc/ build runs 'git log' to stamp the user guide, which fails in the
Bazel sandbox (no git repository present).  We ship no documentation, so
remove doc, samples, win32, vms and misc from the top-level SUBDIRS.  The
resulting build covers include/ and src/ — sufficient to produce the shared
libraries and public headers we actually package.

--- a/Makefile.am
+++ b/Makefile.am
@@ -1,7 +1,7 @@
 ## SUBDIRS determines in which directories automake will generate a Makefile
 ## See also AC_OUTPUT in configure.ac

-SUBDIRS	=	include src doc samples win32 vms misc
+SUBDIRS	=	include src

 ACLOCAL_AMFLAGS = -I m4
